7) 500 grams or more of marijuana;

8) 10 grams or more of other dangerous drugs such as, but 
not limited to, methylenedioxymethamphetamine 
(MDMA) or “ecstasy”, paramethoxyamphetamine (PMA), 
trimethoxyamphetamine (T MA), lysergic acid 
diethylamine (LSD), gamma hydroxybutyrate (GHB), and 
those similarly designed or newly introduced drugs and 
their derivatives, without ha ving any therapeutic value or 
if the quantity possessed is far beyond therapeutic 
requirements, as determined and promulgated by the 
Board in accordance to Section 93, Article XI of this Act.

Otherwise, if the quantity involved is less than the foregoing 
quantities, the penalties shall be graduated as follows:

1) Life imprisonment and a fine ranging from Four hundred 
thousand pesos (P400,000.00) to Five hundred thousand pesos 
(P500,000.00), if the quantity of methamphetamine hydrochloride or 
“shabu” is ten (10) grams or more but less than fifty (50) grams;

